parameters: \N<Yuia>How much time has passed since then...?
\N<Yuia>How long has it been since I was shoved into this place...?
\N<Yuia>Damn it...! This isn't the time to be doing this...!

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, hurry up and move along. Your beloved husband is
just ahead.
\N<Segi>He is... in a place like this...
\N<Segi>Yes... Lord Yuia. It's me. I've come to see you...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, Yuia. How do you like living here? Have you grown a
bit fond of it?
\N<Yuia>Zuuteruka...! You're here too!? What are you doing here!?

\N<Zuuteruka>What am I doing here? I went to the trouble of escorting
your lovely wife all the way down to this dungeon, and this
is how you speak to me?
\N<Yuia>Don't mess with me!! Let me out of here!!

\N<Segi>Lord Yuia... both the child and I are fine. I'm sorry for
making you worry...

\N<Segi>But just a little longer... please bear with it. Everything
will surely work out...
\N<Yuia>What are you saying, it's not your fault...!
\N<Segi>I'm, I'm fine... everything will surely work out.

\N<Segi>So, so please... be at ease. Please... Lord Yuia, be
strong...

\N<Yuia>Accomplish...? What are you talking about? Segi, what do you
mean...?

\N<Segi>Ah... Lord Yuia... I'm so relieved that you're safe. Just
knowing that gives me the strength to persevere. It gives me
hope...

\N<Yuia>Segi, what exactly are you talking about? Can you explain
everything from the beginning...?
\N<Segi>...Yes. That's what I intended when I came here...

\N<Segi>Lord Yuia... there's something I need to report. I've
decided to participate in the military training competition.

\N<Segi>On behalf of Lord Yuia... I-I will fight in the military
training competition. For Lord Yuia's sake... and for Riia's
sake as well.

\N<Yuia>Wh-What do you mean!? Don't tell me Zuuteruka forced you
into this...!

\N<Segi>Mm... No, that's not it... I-I wanted to do this. I've
resolved myself to do what must be done...

\N<Yuia>You decided on your own...!? Do you understand what it means
to participate in the military training competition...!?

\N<Segi>Ah... Ha... That's exactly why. That's why I myself have...
Mmm... decided.

\N<Segi>Because... isn't that right? If I don't step forward...
surely... Riia will be made to stand in my place...

\N<Segi>I can't let that child go through such an ordeal, can I? I
can't put that child in danger, can I?
\N<Segi>Hehe, Lord Yuia. I'm not... mistaken, am I?

\N<Segi>Surely... if Lord Yuia were in my position, you would also
decide to fight to protect that child, wouldn't you...?

\N<Segi>To be honest... it's a little scary, but... even so, I'm
fine... I am.

\N<Segi>Mmm... My feelings for Lord Yuia and Riia... they support my
trembling, cowardly legs...
\N<Segi>It's okay... There's nothing... nothing at all...

\N<Segi>Besides... besides... I've become a bit stronger, you know?
I was able to enter the ruins and come back out again.

\N<Segi>Right? Actually, I have quite a bit of muscle now... It's a
shame I can't show it to Lord Yuia right now.
\N<Segi>So please... believe in me. Leave it to me. Rely on me.

\N<Segi>Like my father and mother, I can protect the one I love. I
can protect you... Please let me protect you.

\N<Segi>Yes... Of course, when it comes to fighting, I'm practically
a novice. Hehe, if only I had asked Lord Yuia to teach me
various things beforehand.

\N<Segi>But don't worry. Irime-san and Rozaro-san... people who are
more expert than me are teaching me various things, and I
will become a woman you can rely on even more than now.

\N<Segi>And then I'll prove it... that I'm not just someone who
needs to be protected.
\N<Yuia>Segi... You're still concerned about that time, aren't you?
\N<Segi>...It would be a lie if I said it wasn't different.

\N<Segi>The memories of my father and mother... and of the Grand
Duke and Princess Consort, they still fiercely shine in my
heart...

\N<Yuia>I feel the same... I was powerless before the threat called
Ryuda. No matter how trivial the situation, my strength was
not enough to overcome it.

\N<Yuia>Even the swordsmanship I devoted myself to, studying under
my father and your father Orugi... it was of no use at all.

\N<Yuia>That's why... Segi. The burden of that time isn't something
you should carry alone.

\N<Yuia>It may not be my place to say this, having been saved at the
expense of your parents... but still, I want you to hear it.
You don't need to feel guilty about what happened then...

\N<Segi>But... even so. I think this is a wall that I must
overcome...

\N<Segi>No, as you said, Lord Yuia... it's a wall that should be
overcome by all of us together—by you, me, and Riia.

\N<Segi>If this detestable adversity is a debt from my past self,
who could do nothing... then it is indeed something that I
must repay now.

\N<Segi>If doing so means... our family can move forward... then I
will continue to push myself, even if it means whipping
myself into action.

\N<Segi>If that is indeed the only way for the three of us in our
family to welcome a bright future... then I will gladly walk
this thorny path.
\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, are you done talking? Looks like it's about time.
\N<Yuia>Zuuteruka...! We didn't call for you! Stay out of this...!

\N<Zuuteruka>That's where you're wrong. Your wife has some very important
business to attend to now.

\N<Segi>Lord Yuia... please don't worry. Didn't I say? I will surely
accomplish it.
\N<Segi>Please believe in me and wait... okay?

\N<Segi>...Your wife might not always seem reliable, but when it
really counts, she might just be someone you can depend on.
